	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65029219"><p>I have ordered stuff thru amazon and had it arrive with missing parts, etc too.  I have ordered stuff "Filled by Amazon" and been sent the wrong product or a different color than I ordered, etc.</p><p>One thing I can say is they have always and immediately generated a return, and either cross shipped a replacement or simply told me to bin the defective/incorrect item or otherwise do what I want with it. Usually with very few questions asked.  It gives me a lot of confidence shopping with them.  It is one of the reasons I'll often pay more for something on Amazon than some other e-tailer etc.  Knowing for certain if there is a problem it won't be 'my' problem is a big draw.</p><p>That said the reason I have so much experience with it is because I buy a lot stuff from them/thru them.  99% there is no problem. I don't buy stuff I don't intent to keep, provided it is as shown/described. I know other people do play games and it sucks because they will ruin it for the rest of us.</p></div>
